Implement graceful shutdown so your app finishes in-flight requests before Docker sends SIGKILL (after the 10-second default timeout).

```javascript
// server.js
const server = app.listen(3000);

// Handle SIGTERM from docker stop
process.on('SIGTERM', () => {
  console.log('SIGTERM received, shutting down gracefully...');
  server.close(() => {
    // Close database connections
    db.end().then(() => {
      console.log('Graceful shutdown complete');
      process.exit(0);
    });
  });

  // Force shutdown after 8 seconds (before Docker's 10s SIGKILL)
  setTimeout(() => {
    console.error('Forced shutdown');
    process.exit(1);
  }, 8000);
});
```

```dockerfile
# Ensure proper signal handling
FROM node:20-slim
# Use dumb-init or tini for signal forwarding
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends dumb-init
ENTRYPOINT ["dumb-init", "--"]
CMD ["node", "server.js"]
```

Increase the stop timeout for apps that need more time:
```yaml
services:
  app:
    stop_grace_period: 30s  # Default is 10s
```

A production-ready Docker daemon configuration with logging, storage, and security settings.

```json
{
  "log-driver": "json-file",
  "log-opts": {
    "max-size": "10m",
    "max-file": "3"
  },
  "storage-driver": "overlay2",
  "live-restore": true,
  "default-ulimits": {
    "nofile": {
      "Name": "nofile",
      "Hard": 65536,
      "Soft": 65536
    }
  },
  "default-address-pools": [
    {
      "base": "172.17.0.0/12",
      "size": 24
    }
  ],
  "metrics-addr": "0.0.0.0:9323",
  "experimental": false,
  "features": {
    "buildkit": true
  },
  "insecure-registries": [],
  "dns": ["8.8.8.8", "8.8.4.4"]
}
```

Key settings: `live-restore` keeps containers running during daemon restarts. `default-ulimits` prevents "too many open files" errors. `metrics-addr` exposes Prometheus metrics. Place this file at `/etc/docker/daemon.json` and restart Docker: `sudo systemctl restart docker`.
